<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11 W 892/48</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Senate Judiciary Committee</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nelson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-21"><hi rend="italic">July 21,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I respectfully beg leave
                            to call your attention to the enclosed bill, S. 3852,<note n="1" xml:id="d206fn1">Not printed.</note> (by Mr. Underwood) ‘to amend an
                            Act entitled “An Act to define, regulate, and punish trading with the
                            enemy, and for other purposes,” approved October 6, 1917, as amended,’
                            and to request that you furnish me, as soon <pb facs="0366" n="252" xml:id="pg_252"/> as may be, for the use of this Committee, with
                            your views, favorable or otherwise, as to the advisability of the
                            legislation proposed in this measure.</p>
                        <p>Yours truly,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knute Nelson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>